# --------------------------------------------------
# Deny by default git ignore list.
#
# This file lists files and patterns that should
# not be tracked by git.
#
# By extension this file is used to exclude files from
# tooling and other processes that rely on git to determine
# which files are part of the project.
#
# We use a deny-by-default approach for the repository root which
# avoids any unwanted auto-generated files from being accidentally
# committed to the repository. The project directory contains its
# own .gitignore file that is based on the classic blacklist approach.
#
# Add files and paths to be tracked by git by adding exceptions:
#
# Add specific file:                        !path/to/file
# Add all files in a directory:             !path/to/directory/
# Add all files in a directory recursively: !path/to/directory/**
# --------------------------------------------------

# Deny by default
*

# Allow directory traversal
!*/

# Allow specific root-level files and directories
!.github/**
!.vscode/**
!profile/**
!.editorconfig
!.git-blame-ignore-revs
!.gitattributes
!.gitignore
!.mailmap
!AUTHORS
!CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
!CONTRIBUTING.md
!GOVERNANCE.md
!LICENSE
!README.md
!SECURITY.md
!SUPPORT.md
